1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:05,630
[Manuel] <i>We're moving on</i>
<i>to the next stage of our plan, Lara.</i>

2
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:09,384
[in English] I hope you are
in the right state of mind.

3
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,010
[woman] <i>General, someone's following Lara.</i>

4
00:00:12,303 --> 00:00:13,638
- [grunting]
- Go ahead!

5
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:15,306
What's going on here?!

6
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:18,977
[Manuel] <i>What are you doing</i>
<i>in front of my house?</i>

7
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:20,395
I'm just doing my job, sir.

8
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:21,604
[Ahmad] <i>Be careful of this man.</i>

9
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:25,358
He's the only one who can
expose your true identity.

10
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:29,863
What are your intentions with the SID?

11
00:00:29,946 --> 00:00:32,949
[Jalil] <i>I just want to know the truth.</i>

12
00:00:33,783 --> 00:00:36,077
[Manuel] <i>That's only for people</i>

13
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:39,539
<i>who are capable of seeing the truth</i>

14
00:00:39,622 --> 00:00:41,666
<i>when it's already right in front of them.</i>

15
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:43,543
[Marcus] <i>We were set up</i>
<i>to turn against each other</i>

16
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:45,295
<i>on the night Datu Rahman was arrested,</i>

17
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,214
<i>and now, they're making him</i>
<i>look like a criminal.</i>

18
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:49,841
<i>But for what?</i>

19
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:52,510
<i>What's their real plan behind all of this?</i>

20
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:54,304
You were so careless!

21
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:56,222
That man followed you!

22
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,058
Why did you mess up now of all times?!

23
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,727
[Lara] Why'd you follow me
all the way to my dad's house, huh?

24
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,896
I just wanted to know what you're hiding.

25
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:04,939
[in English] Are you interrogating me?

26
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:06,357
We'll get there eventually.

27
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,776
[Jalil] <i>Don't be impatient.</i>

28
00:01:08,443 --> 00:01:09,944
[Marcus] <i>I was right.</i>

29
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:12,363
<i>There was another group there that night.</i>

30
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,866
<i>I'll make sure all of you pay,</i>

31
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:17,035
<i>including whoever's behind this.</i>

32
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:19,162
- Harold, you're alive?
- [Harold] What did you do to my friends?!

33
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,705
[grunting]

34
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:24,417
What happened to my friends?!

35
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:31,132
[mysterious theme music playing]

36
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:43,812
- Harold, it's me!
- [tense music playing]

37
00:01:45,396 --> 00:01:47,774
- [grunting]
- [Harold grunts]

38
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:49,734
‪[gasps, growls]

39
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:50,902
[yells]

40
00:01:50,985 --> 00:01:53,238
- [Harold grunts, yells]
- [Marcus] Harold!

41
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:57,200
[both grunting]

42
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:00,328
- [panting]
- Harold!

43
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:02,539
- Harold!
- Felix!

44
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:03,581
Sean!

45
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:04,874
Sir Marcus!

46
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,126
- What's happening to you, Harold?!
- [crying]

47
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:07,710
Help, Sir Marcus!

48
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,087
- Harold!
- Help!

49
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:11,422
- Sir Marcus!
- [ethereal music playing]

50
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:12,674
[breathing heavily]

51
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:14,217
Sean! Let me go!

52
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,344
Oliver, where are you?!

53
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:17,846
Help!

54
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:20,306
Help! I'm alone here!

55
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,891
Sir Marcus, help!

56
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,977
Help!

57
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:26,771
- Help!
- [Ramli] Sir!

58
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:28,314
Sir Rustia!

59
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:29,691
- Sir Rustia!
- [softly] Help!

60
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:31,818
- [breathing heavily]
- Sir! Sir!

61
00:02:31,901 --> 00:02:32,902
- Breathe, sir! Breathe!
- [crying]

62
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:35,155
- Breathe, sir.
- [gasps]

63
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,948
[Harold breathing heavily]

64
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:39,701
What are you doing here?

65
00:02:40,577 --> 00:02:41,953
Why did you come back?

66
00:02:42,036 --> 00:02:44,956
I'm here to find out the truth.

67
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:45,874
‪[breathing heavily]

68
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,877
What happened to Harold?

69
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,336
What do you think?

70
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,171
We had to hide him.

71
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:53,673
A lot of people are angry at him.

72
00:02:53,756 --> 00:02:55,008
At all of you!

73
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:57,427
You killed my fellow villagers!

74
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,889
That's why you shouldn't be seen here!

75
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:03,683
My fellow villagers won't let you live!

76
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:07,812
- [Harold sobbing]
- [Ramli] Sir…

77
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:09,439
[Ramli] Sir.

78
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:16,195
- Harold.
- [fabric flapping]

79
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,867
Do you really not remember me?

80
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:23,494
‪[sighs]

81
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:27,457
There are times
when he's really like that.

82
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,086
Just staring blankly.

83
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:35,215
Sometimes he goes wild,
thinking he's still in the war.

84
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:37,091
But most of the time,
he's looking for all of you.

85
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:42,347
He developed
post-traumatic stress disorder.

86
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,099
[in English] Shell shock.

87
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:48,019
Because of what happened.

88
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:52,190
[morose music playing]

89
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:55,443
I owe Sir Rustia a great debt.

90
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:57,612
Because he saved my son's life.

91
00:03:57,695 --> 00:03:59,822
- Father! Father!
- What happened?

92
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:01,199
He's alive. [heaves]

93
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:04,327
Just take him to the hospital
immediately if possible.

94
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,453
Be careful!

95
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:08,790
Sir!

96
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:09,749
[gunshot]

97
00:04:11,459 --> 00:04:13,628
At first, we thought he was dead.

98
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:18,508
<i>My son and I mourned for him.</i>

99
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,888
[somber music playing]

100
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,441
- Father!
- What?

101
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:47,245
[Ramli] So when we found out
he was still alive,

102
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:48,788
I immediately hid him.

103
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:51,916
Because no matter
how much good Sir Rustia did

104
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,334
for my son,

105
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:57,213
I know my fellow villagers
will never easily forgive

106
00:04:57,922 --> 00:04:59,924
any of you.

107
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:01,801
Especially you.

108
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:06,639
So if I were you, I'd leave now.

109
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:10,018
There'll be chaos
once they find out you're here.

110
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,272
[breathes deeply]

111
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:15,732
I understand.

112
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:19,110
But I'm not leaving

113
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:21,738
until I find out what really happened.

114
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:24,407
What happened?! What really happened?!

115
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:27,994
You came here and slaughtered
my fellow villagers!

116
00:05:28,077 --> 00:05:30,538
That wasn't our plan, believe me.

117
00:05:31,205 --> 00:05:33,583
Another group started
the chaos that night.

118
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:37,879
I found spent bullet casings
from the mountain.

119
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,964
They opened fire from above.

120
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:42,133
They intentionally caused conflict
between our group

121
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:45,094
and your fellow villagers
so there would be bloodshed.

122
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,179
That's what happened!

123
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:49,766
But you still came to arrest Datu Rahman!

124
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:55,354
You arrested him and treated him
like a hardened criminal!

125
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:57,899
There was a warrant of arrest
for Datu Rahman

126
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,276
because of illegal gun smuggling,
and he has to face it!

127
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,111
Those accusations against him aren't true!

128
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:04,614
You want proof?

129
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:08,159
[tense music playing]

130
00:06:13,331 --> 00:06:15,041
Do you think

131
00:06:15,124 --> 00:06:18,127
Allah has forgetten us?

132
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,797
Don't say that, Sitti.

133
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,175
Allah is always listening to us.

134
00:06:25,426 --> 00:06:27,887
But why did our friends die?

135
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,722
Even your father, Harun.

136
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,015
He's gone.

137
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:33,184
[Sitti sniffles] Rania's right.

138
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,604
Why did they take Datu Rahman? [sniffles]

139
00:06:36,687 --> 00:06:40,066
Why did Jamilah leave us?

140
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:43,653
Even Jalil left.

141
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:46,697
He was supposed to protect us.

142
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:50,284
Things aren't the same as they were.

143
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:51,494
[Sitti sobs]

144
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:53,037
Don't say that, Sitti.

145
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:54,372
Don't cry anymore.

146
00:06:54,872 --> 00:06:56,666
Everything will go back to the way it was.

147
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,167
[sniffles]

148
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:00,086
I'm scared.

149
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:04,340
I heard Auntie Aminah.

150
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,425
They say there are people causing trouble

151
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,886
on our neighboring islands.

152
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:11,431
Why are they making us suffer?

153
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:13,891
Are we bad people?

154
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,435
We're not, right?

155
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:19,564
Don't worry, Rania, Sitti.

156
00:07:19,647 --> 00:07:22,984
Allah will look after us.

157
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,902
[crying] I hope…

158
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:32,493
I hope Jalil and Datu Rahman
come back soon.

159
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:36,706
So someone could protect our island again.

160
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:38,666
[sniffles]

161
00:07:38,749 --> 00:07:41,794
I also miss Jamilah very much.

162
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:46,132
[somber music playing]

163
00:07:57,518 --> 00:07:59,145
[grim music playing]

164
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:01,981
[Ramli] That's it.

165
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:05,485
That is proof
that Datu Rahman is innocent.

166
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:06,777
‪[Marcus sighs]

167
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:10,072
This is what Datu Rahman ordered,

168
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,992
that we bury it underground,

169
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,410
so the syndicates couldn't get it.

170
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,246
He didn't want to give them
to the authorities

171
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:19,332
because he didn't know which police

172
00:08:19,415 --> 00:08:21,375
were protecting the syndicates.

173
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:26,797
[Datu Rahman] <i>The weapons I saw,</i>
<i>we got from the sea.</i>

174
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:30,384
And we hid them from the syndicate,
so they couldn't use them.

175
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:36,057
Datu Rahman was right.

176
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,266
[Ramli] He told you the truth!

177
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:38,893
But you don't want to believe him.

178
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:42,480
You didn't just take Datu Rahman
away from us!

179
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,524
You also took our quiet lives!

180
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:48,444
Now, the presence of weapons
is felt all around!

181
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:49,362
‪[heavy breathing]

182
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,033
Even our neighboring islands

183
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:56,285
are being attacked
by pirates and criminals!

184
00:08:58,246 --> 00:08:59,330
It won't be long…

185
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,124
before they attack our island next.

186
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:05,211
[grim music continues]

187
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:09,423
I'll help you.

188
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,759
I will protect you.

189
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,970
We have people protecting us!

190
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,889
It's Datu Rahman. And Jalil.

191
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,225
[dramatic flourish]

192
00:09:19,308 --> 00:09:20,560
Jalil?

193
00:09:22,895 --> 00:09:26,315
‪[heavy breathing, sniffles]

194
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:36,367
Is that Jalil?

195
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:39,036
[breathing heavily] And now
you're after him,

196
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,413
like a criminal?!

197
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:44,083
If he is innocent…

198
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,544
then I need proof.

199
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:47,920
That's the proof!

200
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:51,299
That's the proof that Datu Rahman
and Jalil are innocent.

201
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,092
Is that not enough?!

202
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:54,385
I'm begging you,

203
00:09:54,468 --> 00:09:57,805
respect our mourning and leave!

204
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,267
[inhales sharply]

205
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:02,393
I know…

206
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,522
that what happened here cannot be changed.

207
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:09,859
But I'll make things right.

208
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:15,114
There will be justice
for what happened here.

209
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:17,742
Are you just doing that

210
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,452
to ease your own conscience?

211
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,537
I'm doing this

212
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,665
because it's my job.

213
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:29,170
- Do whatever you want.
- [unsettling music playing]

214
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:31,589
Don't expect us to thank you.

215
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,050
Because no matter what happens,

216
00:10:34,925 --> 00:10:37,511
it won't bring back the lives lost.

217
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:38,846
[inhales]

218
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:42,308
[somber music playing]

219
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:50,024
[tense music playing]

220
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:53,653
[Manuel] <i>What's going on here?</i>

221
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:55,821
[grunts]

222
00:10:57,156 --> 00:11:01,661
[in English] Police Major Allan Espina.

223
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:06,707
I checked all your files.

224
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:09,710
Almost all of them were redacted.

225
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:15,257
Mark my words, I can find

226
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:18,135
everything you're hiding

227
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,137
if I wanted to.

228
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:23,849
[Jalil] <i>I can't</i>
<i>figure out General Carillo.</i>

229
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:25,726
<i>But…</i>

230
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,145
<i>was he able to figure me out?</i>

231
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:30,564
<i>Did he know that I was hiding something?</i>

232
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:35,236
[melancholic music playing]

233
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:42,076
[engine sputtering]

234
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:49,041
- [sighs]
- [handbreak creaks]

235
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,437
[melancholic music continues]

236
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:14,358
[disconnected signal beeping]

237
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:44,096
Harold…

238
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:48,601
I have to go for now.

239
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,730
I'm going back to Manila.

240
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:57,985
I'm sorry, I can't take you with me.

241
00:12:58,068 --> 00:13:00,070
I can't put your life in danger.

242
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,574
We don't know what'd happen

243
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:05,993
if our attackers find out you're alive.

244
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,915
[somber music playing]

245
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:14,793
[sighs deeply]

246
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:18,506
But I promise you…

247
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,635
I'll come back for you,

248
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:26,597
whatever happens.

249
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:32,353
Everything's gonna be fine.

250
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:35,898
[Jalil] Doctor?

251
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:41,487
Wait…

252
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:46,700
You're my son's new co-worker
at SID, right?

253
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,787
The one who saved me
from the hostage-takers.

254
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:52,831
[chuckles] What's your name, by the way?

255
00:13:54,124 --> 00:13:56,043
[in English] Police Major Allan Espina.

256
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,298
What happened?

257
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:03,717
I don't know. It just stalled.

258
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,594
I'm trying to call my son…

259
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:06,804
I'll take care of it.

260
00:14:06,887 --> 00:14:09,807
- [car door clicks open]
- Uh… Are you sure?

261
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,350
- [soft chuckle] Yes, Doctor.
- [lever clicks]

262
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:13,686
Wait here, please.

263
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:18,399
[gentle music playing]

264
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,114
‪[inhales]

265
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:29,785
‪[exhales]

266
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:39,003
‪[deep breath]

267
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:40,754
I know…

268
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:44,675
I have no right to ask you for favors.

269
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:47,011
But I hope…

270
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:51,724
I hope you take care of Harold.

271
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,144
Because of him,

272
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,437
my son is alive.

273
00:14:57,771 --> 00:14:59,315
You have nothing to worry about.

274
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:01,775
We will take care of him.

275
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,695
I would like to apologize
to the townspeople.

276
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:08,824
Though, I know I can't
bring back the lives lost.

277
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:13,245
I'd probably just satisfy
my own conscience if I do that.

278
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:16,999
But even though I can't change anything,

279
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:22,087
I'll still fix what I can.

280
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:26,926
I'll make sure

281
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:30,554
that I find out who's behind all of this.

282
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,431
[music turns dramatic]

283
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:40,689
[sighs deeply]

284
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:42,900
Please be safe.

285
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:07,257
[uneasy music playing]

286
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:12,388
Madam!

287
00:16:18,018 --> 00:16:19,770
[clicks tongue] Madam.

288
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:24,233
I saw you talking angrily to Espina.

289
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,236
Did he do something bad?

290
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:29,697
How did you know?
Are you stalking me, too?

291
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:34,034
Espina was stalking you?

292
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,536
Yes.

293
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:38,539
He followed me home and all the way here.

294
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:42,793
Why would he stalk you?

295
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:46,755
Because he's investigating me.

296
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:47,965
All of us.

297
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:52,177
Madam, don't let him get into your head.

298
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,346
Just say the word,

299
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:55,889
and I'll deal with him.

300
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,349
[scoffs] And what?

301
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,019
[in English] Attract
unnecessary attention?

302
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,730
We don't even know who sent him.

303
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:05,399
We don't know his mission
in going into NLEA.

304
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:10,487
- We can't let him succeed.
- [in English] Then, we stay ahead.

305
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:14,491
So, don't do anything unless Dad says so.

306
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:17,369
[approaching footsteps]

307
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:20,873
[in English] General is ready for you.

308
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,583
- [Felix] Madam.
- [sighs]

309
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,252
Just as I said…

310
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:27,129
[in English] Just say the word.

311
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:28,672
[scoffs]

312
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:38,515
- Oh!
- Hi.

313
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,641
- Oh, hi.
- Hi.

314
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:41,769
[kisses]

315
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:43,270
How was your day?

316
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:44,980
[in English] Well, the usual. [sighs]

317
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,315
Exhausting.

318
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,692
Oh, by the way.

319
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:51,278
Our daughter called me on video call.

320
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:52,988
- She was looking for you.
- Really?

321
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,783
- How's Jackie? Why did she call?
- [chuckles]

322
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:58,077
She said she has some special news.

323
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,369
Look.

324
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,956
Jackie is pregnant!

325
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,416
‪[gentle music playing]

326
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:07,169
Yes!

327
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:10,130
We will be grandparents soon!

328
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,924
Grandma and Grandpa.

329
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:13,342
And because of that,

330
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:17,679
she's also asking when we can go to visit.

331
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:19,473
[sighs]

332
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:25,687
If you ask me,
I'd fly right now to the US.

333
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,607
But you know how it is.

334
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:30,567
[sighs]

335
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:34,655
- Oh, by the way, Robert…
- [Azuelo] What?

336
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,990
He said he wants to visit us this weekend.

337
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:38,784
- He said he wanted to have lunch.
- [in English] Good.

338
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:39,785
[in English] Very good!

339
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:42,246
Well, I've been missing that kid too.

340
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:45,207
Our babies have all grown up now, huh?

341
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:47,709
Good thing Kyle is still here with us.

342
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:50,295
He may still be with us, but look at him!

343
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,673
He's nose-deep in his gadget!

344
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:53,841
[giggles]

345
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:56,135
- Hey.
- [taps]

346
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:57,302
Kyle!

347
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,596
Hey. What's up, Dad?

348
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:01,890
Put your gadget down first, son.

349
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,725
We're at the dining table.

350
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:05,060
- But--
- [in English] Put it down.

351
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,566
[Azuelo sighs]

352
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:18,157
"BRB…" [muttering]

353
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:20,450
- [stomps]
- What are you so busy with?

354
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:22,578
Uh, it's CUBIX, Dad.

355
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:23,912
Uh, it's a gaming app.

356
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:26,039
There are a lot
of user-generated games here

357
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:27,207
that you can play, Dad.

358
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,835
Oh, check this out!
I'm talking to someone.

359
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:34,173
Well, who are you talking to?

360
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:37,718
Uh, nobody, Dad. Just some online friends.

361
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:39,803
[in English] Online friends, huh?

362
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:41,638
Well, that's…

363
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,974
Hmm… Be extremely cautious.

364
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,019
You don't know those users
personally, son.

365
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:48,478
It could be dangerous.

366
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:51,023
No, Dad. Don't worry.

367
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:55,652
Well, let's eat first, alright? Okay?

368
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:59,865
Put aside your games for now.

369
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:04,578
Because you've been playing way too much!

370
00:20:04,661 --> 00:20:06,914
[in English] You have to eat, son!

371
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:08,248
So that…

372
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,709
- [smacks]
- You'll gain some muscles!

373
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:11,793
[wife laughing]

374
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:13,545
- [wife] Oh, you!
- [Azuelo] You're all games!

375
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:15,255
- You'll be all lanky!
- [giggles]

376
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:23,305
This is just a temporary fix, Doc.

377
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,641
You should still have it checked.

378
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:26,934
Thank you so much.

379
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:29,770
Normally, Marcus fixes it for me, but…

380
00:20:29,853 --> 00:20:32,981
I couldn't contact my son
'cause my phone died.

381
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,400
Marcus is on leave.

382
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:36,818
You didn't know?

383
00:20:37,527 --> 00:20:38,862
Huh? No.

384
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:41,949
Oh, that child…
He didn't tell me anything.

385
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:44,451
[sighs] Good thing you came.

386
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:47,120
Thank you very much once again.

387
00:20:47,204 --> 00:20:49,790
It's nothing. I'll take my leave then.

388
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:51,708
Take care, Doc.

389
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:55,254
Wait! Aren't you hungry?

390
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:56,755
I know!

391
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:58,215
You should have dinner with me.

392
00:20:58,298 --> 00:21:00,259
Marcus isn't here anyway.

393
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,052
Ah… It's okay.

394
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:04,346
- I don't want to impose.
- Oh, you.

395
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:06,056
Not only did you save me at the hospital,

396
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:07,224
but also now too.

397
00:21:07,307 --> 00:21:09,518
Come on. At least let me…

398
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,395
make it up to you.

399
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:14,773
Plus I want to get to know
Marcus' friends too.

400
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:21,238
Alright. I'll go.

401
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:24,616
[emotional music playing]

402
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:28,745
How's your search for Datu Rahman?

403
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:31,373
[in English] I'm still working
on it, Dad. Um…

404
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:33,292
I'm currently trying to find out
his location.

405
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:37,129
[in English] So, you got nothing?

406
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:40,549
I thought you said

407
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:44,136
you wanted to avenge your parents?

408
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:47,264
Th-- That's right.

409
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:50,225
Then why haven't you found him yet?

410
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,313
[in English] You know damn well

411
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:58,108
that Datu Rahman is a crucial piece
to our chess game.

412
00:21:58,191 --> 00:22:01,778
That he is our most convenient fall guy,

413
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,489
so that everyone in the country
would think

414
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:08,410
that all thi chaos
is caused by a syndicate!

415
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:11,872
And so that no one could figure out

416
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:15,584
the destabilization that we're doing!

417
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:18,253
[in English] When will you stop
disappointing me?!

418
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:21,173
[tense music playing]

419
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,800
[in English] I will make you proud, Dad.

420
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:27,179
- [sighs]
- [Lara, in English] I will make you proud.

421
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:28,096
[scoffs]

422
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,140
[Manuel sighs]

423
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,225
[in English] Show me.

424
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:39,316
[door clicks shut]

425
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:41,610
[line rings]

426
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:42,694
Hello?

427
00:22:43,653 --> 00:22:45,155
[sighs] Any news about my order?

428
00:22:45,238 --> 00:22:47,991
[man] <i>Ma'an, we're still tailing Sabdani.</i>

429
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:51,078
Okay. Don't let him out of your sight.

430
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:52,496
[in English] I need results.

431
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:53,914
‪[sinister music playing]

432
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:58,627
[Felix] Lara, what's the matter?

433
00:22:58,710 --> 00:23:01,129
- What do you care?
- Where are you going?

434
00:23:01,713 --> 00:23:03,673
You know, if you're gonna do something,

435
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:05,884
you don't have to do it alone.

436
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,427
I can help you.

437
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:08,678
I'm here.

438
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:13,892
[sighs]

439
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:14,976
[in English] Look.

440
00:23:15,894 --> 00:23:17,354
[in English] Whenever you're around,

441
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,523
people end up dead.

442
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,150
So, leave me alone.

443
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,485
[suspenseful sting]

444
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:27,197
[tense music playing]

445
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,999
[Marcus] <i>Gabriel.</i>

446
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:41,169
<i>You are my inspiration in everything I do.</i>

447
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:42,295
- [Gabriel] <i>Marcus!</i>
- [young Marcus] <i>Gabriel!</i>

448
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:44,422
[Marcus] <i>I want to save people</i>

449
00:23:45,215 --> 00:23:48,176
<i>because it's the one thing</i>
<i>I wasn't able to do for you.</i>

450
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:51,638
I just suddenly remembered my late son.

451
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:53,557
[Teresa] <i>Gabriel.</i>

452
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,810
<i>It's been 30 years</i>
<i>since he drowned in the ocean.</i>

453
00:23:56,893 --> 00:24:01,606
<i>I can't help but be sad</i>
<i>whenever I remember him.</i> [sniffles]

454
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:04,609
Whenever we lose a loved one,

455
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:07,195
the pain never really heals.

456
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:09,322
[Jalil] <i>We just grow numb to it.</i>

457
00:24:09,406 --> 00:24:11,658
Jalil, my son… Jalil…

458
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:13,952
[Lara] <i>Any news</i>
<i>on what I ordered you to do?</i>

459
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:16,037
[man] <i>They're heading</i>
<i>to an abandoned place.</i>

460
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,330
Looks like they're hiding something.

461
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:19,124
[suspenseful music playing]

462
00:24:19,207 --> 00:24:20,625
Is this the right location?

463
00:24:24,212 --> 00:24:25,380
[Marcus] <i>I promise you.</i>

464
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:28,633
<i>I will solve this case.</i>

465
00:24:29,759 --> 00:24:32,554
<i>So they won't have any more victims.</i>

466
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:36,308
[music concludes]
